			Company Description 


			G-III Apparel Group Ltd. Manufactures and distributes outerwear and sportswear.  It operates through the following business segments: Wholesale Operations and Retail Operations business.  The Wholesale Operations segment consists of products and non-licensed products segments. It also includes sales...
		


                G-III Apparel Group Ltd. Manufactures and distributes outerwear and sportswear.  It operates through the following business segments: Wholesale Operations and Retail Operations business.  The Wholesale Operations segment consists of products and non-licensed products segments. It also includes sales of products under the company's licensed brands. The Retail Operations segment includes Wilsons Leather and G.H. Bass stores, as well as Calvin Klein Performance stores. The company provides apparel under recognized brands to retailers such as Macy's, Bloomingdale's, Nordstrom, Lord and Taylor, The Bon-Ton Stores, Dillards, JC Penney, and Kohl's. It also has fashion licenses under Calvin Klein, Sean John, Kenneth Cole, Cole Haan, Guess?, Jones New York, Jessica Simpson, Vince Camuto, Nine West, Ellen Tracy, Tommy Hilfiger, Kensie, Mac and Jac, Levi's, and Dockers brands. G-III Apparel Group was founded by Aron Goldfarb in 1974 and is headquartered in New York, NY.
            




